      "arguments": {
        "file_path": "/workspace/django/test/client.py",
        "old_string": "class AsyncRequestFactory(RequestFactory):\n    \"\"\"\n    Class that lets you create mock ASGI-like Request objects for use in\n    testing. Usage:\n\n    rf = AsyncRequestFactory()\n    get_request = rf.get(\"/hello/\")\n    post_request = rf.post(\"/submit/\", {\"foo\": \"bar\"})\n\n    Once you have a request object you can pass it to any view function,\n    including synchronous ones. The reason we have a separate class here is:\n    a) this makes ASGIRequest subclasses, and\n    b) AsyncClient can subclass it.\n    \"\"\"",
        "new_string": "class AsyncRequestFactory(TestRequestBuilder):\n    \"\"\"\n    Class that lets you create mock ASGI-like Request objects for use in\n    testing. Usage:\n\n    rf = AsyncRequestFactory()\n    get_request = rf.get(\"/hello/\")\n    post_request = rf.post(\"/submit/\", {\"foo\": \"bar\"})\n\n    Once you have a request object you can pass it to any view function,\n    including synchronous ones. The reason we have a separate class here is:\n    a) this makes ASGIRequest subclasses, and\n    b) AsyncClient can subclass it.\n    \"\"\"",
